# PART 4: TOWER REGISTRATION

## The Registration Desk

A simple desk stands at the base of the Tower entrance — clean, official-looking, slightly out of place given everything around it. There is a form on the desk with a quill.

**The Form:**
```
TOWER CLIMBER REGISTRATION
——————————————————————————
Party Name:        ________________
Leader Name:       ________________
Member 1:          ________________
Member 2:          ________________
Member 3:          ________________
Class(es):         ________________
Origin:            ________________
Acknowledged Tower Waiver: [ ]
```

**DM Note:** The "waiver" is one line of small text that reads: *The Tower accepts no liability for quarrels, misunderstandings, bruised egos, uncomfortable silences, or the accidental revelation of embarrassing secrets."* Let the players read it if they want.

**No one is visibly staffing the desk.** The form seems to be self-administered. When both players begin filling it out, read:

> *The quill moves across the paper of its own accord, tracing over the names you write as if confirming them. The Tower hums once — low, resonant, felt in the chest more than heard. Then: silence.*

