## The Masked Girl

> *She is standing behind you when you turn around. She was not there before.*
>
> *She is wearing a plain white mask that covers the upper half of her face — simple, smooth, with no decoration. Her clothes are nondescript, her expression unreadable below the mask. She is holding your completed registration form and reading it.*
>
> *Slowly.*
>
> *She has been reading the same two lines — the names — for several seconds longer than necessary.*

**⚠️ DM Note — Insight Check:** Ask all players to make a Passive Insight check, or call for an active one. DC 12.

- **Success:** *There is something in the way she holds the paper — not surprise, exactly. Recognition. Like she is confirming something she already suspected, not discovering something new. The pause is deliberate.*
- **Failure:** *She seems to be reviewing the form carefully. Thorough, maybe.*

**The Masked Girl** *[sets the form down, looks at both of them, and speaks with a voice that carries without being loud]:*

*"Byron Engel. Shuu Seiji. Outside-world humans."*

*[Beat.]*

*"You are hereby recognized as Official Climbers of the Tower. Welcome."*

*[She produces two small tokens — dark metal, warm to the touch, etched with a simple spiral — and holds them out.]*

