>
> *It is daytime — or something that looks like daytime, warm and golden, with a sky that is almost convincing. The air smells of shrine incense and pine. The architecture is old — weathered stone lanterns, worn wooden gates, a red torii in the distance. You are standing in the outer grounds of what appears to be a ruined version of a Shinto shrine.*
